All Covid-19 data reported in the is app is from The New York Times Covid-19 data set which is based on reports from state and local health agencies. Their data can be found here: https://github.com/nytimes/covid-19-data. The data was used to calculate some of the statistics in this app. Data reported in this app may differ from other sources due to differences in reporting standards and reporting lag times.

This app is designed to provide users with an overview of the Covid-19 information in their area. This apps uses a user\'s location in order to alert them of the Covid-19 status in areas they have visited or are currently visiting. This app is not designed as a contact tracing app and should not be used as such. This app is provided purely for informational purposes.
Notifies whenever entering an area with high community spread
Notifies whenever an area visited in the last 14 days has high community spread
Current Location Settings must be enabled for full functionality of this app. This app does not work without current location enabled. Current location data is only saved as county.
